SIMPLE: huzza
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Huzza
<hw>Huz*za"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>hussa</ets>, <ets>husa</ets>, interj., hurrah, huzza. ⟦root⟧43. Cf.
<er>Hurrah</er>.]</ety> <def>A word used as a shout of joy, exultation,
approbation, or encouragement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huzza</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Huzza
<hw>Huz"za</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shout of <xex>huzza</xex>; a
cheer; a hurrah.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They made a great <qex>huzza</qex> or shout.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huzza</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Huzza
<hw>Huz*za"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Huzzaed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Huzzaing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To shout huzza; to
cheer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huzza</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Huzza
<hw>Huz*za"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To receive or attend with
huzzas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was <qex>huzzaed</qex> into the court.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hy</ent>⟦br⟧
